x4freetext: The Al absorber was used with the main target out
and acted as a dummy target. The Au foil was
inserted with the main target in position in order
to reduce the beam intensity and ensure similar
geometry of the beam during the measurement of the
zero effect with the dummy target.
Each of the passing counters consisted of a
piece of NE 102 plastic scintillator foil of
to the surface of the photocathode of the EMI 6097
photomultiplier). A good light collection was secured
by a parabolic cavity covered with a magnesium oxide
deposit. The obtained energy resolution of 27% was
The end counter consisted of a Csl(Tl) crystal
of 30 mm diam and of thickness slightly larger than the
range of 25MeV alpha particles in the scintillation
material. The crystal was glued on a surface of the
photomultiplier and covered by a thin aluminized
melinex foil. The counter collected the particles
coming from the target inside of the angle +- 50.degr.
The energy resolution of the end counter was better
SD:REACTION code at Subent 010 was corrected
